---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Work — Pauls Workshop" description="Selected projects: Azure solutions, Copilot agents, and enterprise platform work.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 24px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">portfolio</p>
      <h1>Selected work</h1>
      <p class="lede muted">
        Real engagements, from requirements to running solution. Each project
        here typically has one or more companion articles in the blog.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="border-top: none; padding-top: 24px;">
    <div class="wrap project-grid">
      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">SharePoint · Python · SQLite · scikit-learn</p>
        <h3>IT Support Knowledge Base Mining</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Turned six years and 146,000 raw IT tickets into a clean, reviewed
          knowledge base — schema recon, ETL into SQLite, unsupervised
          clustering, and LLM-drafted articles with a privacy safety net.
          Foundation for the IT support agent below.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Data engineer & pipeline author</p>
        <p class="muted"><a class="more" href="/blog/blog-mining-tickets-into-knowledge/">Read the article →</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">React Native · Expo · .NET API · Azure</p>
        <h3>Greenport — Environmental Compliance Platform</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Cross-platform (web + iOS/Android) compliance logging app for
          multi-client, multi-site environmental data capture: waste
          tracking, energy/water logs, observations, and package-status
          workflows. Built end-to-end — React Native/Expo front end, .NET
          API on Azure App Service, Logic Apps and WebJobs for automation,
          Entra B2C auth, and Key Vault-secured data access.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Full-stack developer (front end, API, and Azure infrastructure)</p>
        <p class="muted"><a class="more" href="https://www.keo.com/greenport" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View product →</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">Microsoft 365 · Copilot · Governance</p>
        <h3>AI Administration & agent governance</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Ongoing platform work inside an enterprise Microsoft 365 tenant:
          AI Administrator RBAC scope, Copilot Credits and licensing strategy,
          and governance with Entra Agent ID, Purview, and Defender.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> AI Administrator</p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">SPFx · React · Fluent UI · PnPjs</p>
        <h3>KEO Holiday Calendar (SharePoint Web Part)</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A reusable SharePoint Framework web part that surfaces company
          holidays across SharePoint, Teams, and Outlook — pulling from a
          SharePoint list via PnPjs, with multi-country flag support,
          tentative-vs-confirmed styling, date-range filtering, and both a
          compact "Home" view and a filterable "Detail" view. Fully
          configurable through the property pane — no code changes needed
          to reuse across sites.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Solo developer</p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">SPFx · React · Fluent UI · Graph Toolkit</p>
        <h3>KEO Greetings (SharePoint Web Part)</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A SharePoint Framework web part that celebrates employee birthdays
          and work anniversaries — pulls from a SharePoint list, renders
          Persona cards with photos via Microsoft Graph Toolkit grouped as
          Today / Tomorrow / Upcoming, tabbed Birthdays/Anniversaries views,
          and a confetti animation for the day's birthdays. Fully
          configurable through the property pane.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Solo developer</p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">Python · python-docx · Azure Blob Storage · matplotlib</p>
        <h3>Compliance Report Automation (Azure WebJob)</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A Python Azure WebJob that generates a monthly compliance report
          end-to-end: pulls consolidated log data (observations, energy,
          water, wastewater, waste, hazardous materials, training, and
          environmental monitoring) from an API, builds bar, pie, and
          wind-rose charts, fills a Word template via a custom
          placeholder-replacement engine, then uploads the finished report
          to Azure Blob Storage and emails it to the requester.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Solo developer</p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">Copilot Studio · Agents SDK · Foundry</p>
        <h3>Agent build lab (in progress)</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          A structured build programme across declarative agents, custom
          engine agents, and Azure AI Foundry — documented step by step in
          the articles section as it happens.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Builder & author</p>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="stack">Azure · React · BRD · Proposal</p>
        <h3>Visitor Gate Pass Management System</h3>
        <p class="muted">
          Full design-and-delivery engagement for a cloud-based visitor
          management system: business requirements document, solution
          architecture on Azure, working React prototype, cost estimation,
          and a client-ready proposal and quotation.
        </p>
        <p class="muted"><strong>Role:</strong> Solution designer & developer</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
